                    ☛ He grew up in a close-knit family with his father, Jorge Messi, who worked as a factory steel worker, and his mother, Celia, who was a cleaner. He has two older brothers and a sister. <br><br>
        
                    ☛ Messi joined FC Barcelona's youth academy, La Masia, at the age of 13. He made his first-team debut in 2004 and became the club's all-time top scorer.<br><br>
        
                    ☛ Messi has represented Argentina in several international tournaments, including the FIFA World Cup and Copa América. He led Argentina to victory in the 2021 Copa América and the 2022 FIFA World Cup. <br><br>
        
